Single-molecule tracking (SMT) data from the literature [1,2,3,4] are available to test various condensate-constrained models of E-P communication. 

[1] H. Chen, M. Levo, L. Barinov, M. Fujioka, J. B. Jaynes, and T. Gregor, Dynamic interplay between enhancer–promoter topology and gene activity, Nat. Genet. 50, 1296 (2018).
[2] J. M. Alexander, J. Guan, B. Li, L. Maliskova, M. Song, Y. Shen, B. Huang, S. Lomvardas, and O. D. Weiner, Live-cell imaging reveals enhancer-dependent Sox2 transcription in the absence of enhancer proximity, eLife 8, e41769 (2019).
[3] D. B. Brückner, H. Chen, L. Barinov, B. Zoller, and T. Gregor, Stochastic motion and transcriptional dynamics of pairs of distal DNA loci on a compacted chromosome, Science 380, 1357
(2023).
[4] P. Mach, P. I. Kos, Y. Zhan, J. Cramard, S. Gaudin, J. Tünnermann, E. Marchi, J. Eglinger, J. Zuin,M. Kryzhanovska, S. Smallwood, L. Gelman, G. Roth, E. P. Nora, G. Tiana, and L.
Giorgetti, Cohesin and CTCF control the dynamics of chromosome folding, Nat. Genet. 54, 1907 (2022).
